snippet: Rail services had resumed after almost 200 migrants broke through security near the opening of the Channel Tunnel in France, clashing with police officers and forcing a temporary suspension of service.
abstract: Group of around 200 migrants break through security fence at Channel Tunnel entrance in France, with some reaching as far as nine miles into tunnel before being turned back by French police; action by such a large group appears to be more of plea to recognize crisis, as they had little chance of reaching England.
